HEADWORD: Calorifere
<hw>Ca*lor"i*fere</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>calorif⟦egrave⟧re</ets>, fr. L. <ets>calor</ets> heat +
<ets>ferre</ets> to bear.]</ety> <def>An apparatus for conveying and
distributing heat, especially by means of hot water circulating in
tubes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calorifiant</ent>⟦br⟧
